## Important Notes

- The `encoded_setting_xml` field is marked as sensitive and will not be displayed in logs or plan output
- You can use either `encoded_setting_xml` for XML-based configuration or the `settings` block for structured configuration, but not both simultaneously
- When using `settings`, the supported `app_config_key_type` values are:
  - `stringType`
  - `integerType`
  - `realType`
  - `booleanType`
  - `tokenType`
- The `assignments` block supports the following `odata_type` values:
  - `#microsoft.graph.allLicensedUsersAssignmentTarget` - Targets all licensed users
  - `#microsoft.graph.allDevicesAssignmentTarget` - Targets all devices
  - `#microsoft.graph.groupAssignmentTarget` - Targets a specific group (requires `group_id`)
  - `#microsoft.graph.exclusionGroupAssignmentTarget` - Excludes a specific group (requires `group_id`)
- Assignment IDs are automatically generated by the API and preserved during updates

